Three people have been injured after a red bakkie and minibus taxi collided with each other on the N4 direction Nelspruit next to Ilanga Mall, Mpumalanga on the weekend.According to paramedics the accident happened at about 21h20.All patients were stabilised on scene by Netcare 911 paramedics and other private services before they were taken to hospital.A secondary accident occurred when a bakkie collided with one of the vehicles involved in the accident.From that accident three people were treated for moderate to minor injuries before being transported to various hospitals in the area for further medical care.-TNA Reporter